She'll have him sprint up here
in his helicopter...

712
00:55:41,053 --> 00:55:43,054
...if you can produce ghosts for her.

713
00:55:45,016 --> 00:55:46,182
Oh, Charles.

714
00:55:47,101 --> 00:55:49,769
I should remind you all
that I am Delia's agent.

715
00:55:49,937 --> 00:55:52,522
I have consistently lost money
on her work for years.

716
00:55:52,690 --> 00:55:55,191
If anything actually happened here,
I shall handle it.

717
00:55:55,359 --> 00:55:57,652
But not until I致e seen some real proof.

718
00:55:57,820 --> 00:56:01,656
-But, Bernard, what about this table?
-What just happened, what was that?

719
00:56:01,824 --> 00:56:03,700
And what money?
Don't you believe in my work?

720
00:56:03,868 --> 00:56:05,118
CHARLES:
Uh-uh-uh!

721
00:56:05,286 --> 00:56:06,828
Here's Lydia.

722
00:56:07,622 --> 00:56:10,540
-Well?
-They don't want to come down.

723
00:56:11,751 --> 00:56:13,460
DELIA:
Charles.

724
00:56:17,882 --> 00:56:19,716
Why not?

725
00:56:20,509 --> 00:56:25,138
I think the reason is that they were trying to
scare you away, and you didn't get scared.

726
00:56:25,806 --> 00:56:28,975
Please, they're dead.
It's a little late to be neurotic.

727
00:56:32,396 --> 00:56:33,772
All right.

728
00:56:39,779 --> 00:56:43,865
This was not a hallucination.
This was real.

729
00:56:44,033 --> 00:56:49,162
We all just experienced a very super-powerful
paranormal experience and it was real.

730
00:56:49,330 --> 00:56:53,375
Delia, you are a flake.
You have always been a flake.

731
00:56:53,542 --> 00:56:57,212
If you insist on frightening people,
do it with your sculpture.

732
00:56:59,131 --> 00:57:00,507
CHARLES:
Drive carefully.

733
00:57:00,675 --> 00:57:02,592
-I知 dead.
-Where do they hide out?

734
00:57:03,177 --> 00:57:05,845
-The attic.
-The attic's locked.

735
00:57:06,305 --> 00:57:08,515
They're ghosts, Dad.
They can do what they want.

736
00:57:08,683 --> 00:57:12,352
Yeah, they do whatever they want.
Lydia, you take us up there right now.

737
00:57:18,109 --> 00:57:21,444
Fabulous. Otho Fenlock's
"Locked Door Ghosts."

738
00:57:21,612 --> 00:57:23,196
Probably committed suicide up there.

739
00:57:23,364 --> 00:57:25,532
-I知 totally enchanted.
DELIA: They're in there?

740
00:57:25,700 --> 00:57:28,618
-They must live like animals.
-It痴 locked. How did they get in?

741
00:57:28,786 --> 00:57:31,579
Open this door, you dead people,
or we'll bust it down...

742
00:57:31,747 --> 00:57:34,416
...and drag you out by the ropes
you hanged yourself with.

743
00:57:34,583 --> 00:57:36,793
-They didn't commit suicide.
-It doesn't matter.

744
00:57:36,961 --> 00:57:40,380
I have a chance to teach you something.
Take the upper hand in all situations...

745
00:57:40,548 --> 00:57:43,216
...or people, whether dead or alive,
will walk all over you.

746
00:57:43,384 --> 00:57:45,385
Open up!

747
00:57:57,106 --> 00:57:58,690
So where are they?

748
00:57:58,858 --> 00:58:01,401
Listen, you guys, these ghosts
are really nice people.

749
00:58:01,569 --> 00:58:04,904
I think we scared them away,
so let's just leave them alone, all right?

750
00:58:05,197 --> 00:58:08,616
It's the whole damn town.

751
00:58:09,368 --> 00:58:13,997
I have never been so embarrassed.
They haven't gone for good, have they?

752
00:58:14,832 --> 00:58:16,499
Hmm.

753
00:58:20,421 --> 00:58:24,674
CHARLES: Beep, beep.
-Dad, don't. Mom, let's just go.

754
00:58:36,520 --> 00:58:38,104
No ghosts here.

755
00:58:40,900 --> 00:58:43,818
Come on. lf they are in here,
I don't want to scare them away.

756
00:58:46,363 --> 00:58:49,407
Well, we're leaving now.
You can go about your business.

757
00:58:51,786 --> 00:58:54,621
CHARLES: What are we doing?
DELIA: Quick, quick, quick.

758
00:58:58,334 --> 00:59:00,627
[BETELGEUSE LAUGHING]

759
00:59:01,962 --> 00:59:05,799
Oh, boy. You guys are really a couple of
spooksters, aren't you?

760
00:59:05,966 --> 00:59:09,636
Now, let's turn on the juice
and see what shakes loose.

761
00:59:12,389 --> 00:59:15,850
Otho, you get Maxie on the phone.
We've really got something here.

762
00:59:16,018 --> 00:59:20,146
We can turn this place into the world's
leading supernatural research center.

763
00:59:20,314 --> 00:59:23,483
An amusement park. I'll do a presentation.
Lydia will bring the ghosts.

764
00:59:23,651 --> 00:59:26,444
I can't bring the ghosts, Dad.
They're not here.

765
00:59:26,612 --> 00:59:31,032
-Otho, can't you do something?
-Perhaps. If I知 properly motivated.

766
00:59:33,077 --> 00:59:35,829
Just what type of motivation
do you require, Otho?

767
00:59:35,996 --> 00:59:39,582
LYDIA: Why don't you leave them alone?
They didn't do anything to you.

768
00:59:40,251 --> 00:59:41,584
[RATTLING]

769
00:59:48,175 --> 00:59:49,217
[DELIA GASPS]

770
00:59:50,094 --> 00:59:51,719
[HISSING]
Hi.

771
00:59:51,887 --> 00:59:56,933
[SCREAMS]

772
00:59:57,101 --> 00:59:58,226
[CHUCKLING]

773
01:00:07,695 --> 01:00:09,362
Whoa!

774
01:00:10,739 --> 01:00:12,740
[BETELGEUSE LAUGHS]

775
01:00:27,548 --> 01:00:29,757
We've come for your daughter, Chuck.

776
01:00:30,926 --> 01:00:32,260
Stop. Stop.

777
01:00:37,474 --> 01:00:38,641
Yeah.

778
01:00:43,981 --> 01:00:46,774
-Betelgeuse, Betelgeuse, Betelgeuse.
-Oh, no.

779
01:00:49,528 --> 01:00:51,112
Why are you doing this?

780
01:00:52,323 --> 01:00:54,574
Leave me alone, all of you.

781
01:00:58,454 --> 01:01:00,914
Great choice we got here.
We spend the next century...

782
01:01:01,081 --> 01:01:03,541
...either hanging out the window
or doing parlor tricks.

783
01:01:03,709 --> 01:01:06,336
Maybe they'll leave now.
That snake was a nasty customer.

784
01:01:06,503 --> 01:01:08,504
-Well, he could've hurt somebody.
-But he didn't.

785
01:01:08,672 --> 01:01:11,132
We've got them
right where we want them.

786
01:01:15,220 --> 01:01:19,265
You bunch of losers. How dare you interrupt
a professional while he's working.

787
01:01:19,433 --> 01:01:22,018
I'm not fond of Charles Deetz particularly,
but you could've killed him.

788
01:01:22,186 --> 01:01:25,355
Hey, I'm just doing my job.
Besides, I thought we had a deal.

789
01:01:26,190 --> 01:01:28,650
Hey, it's okay. You know why?

790
01:01:28,817 --> 01:01:32,403
I don't wanna do business
with you deadbeats anyway, thank you.

791
01:01:32,571 --> 01:01:36,366
The only one I think I can deal with
is Edgar Allan Poe's daughter.

792
01:01:36,533 --> 01:01:38,868
-I think she understands me.
-You leave her alone, you--

793
01:01:39,870 --> 01:01:41,371
Ow!

794
01:01:51,256 --> 01:01:53,549
Go ahead, make my millennium.

795
01:01:53,717 --> 01:01:56,386
[LAUGHING]

796
01:01:58,233 --> 01:02:03,233
[CLEARS THROAT]

797
01:01:59,556 --> 01:02:00,932
Yeah.

798
01:02:01,100 --> 01:02:05,019
I'm feeling a little, uh, ooh, anxious,
if you know what I mean.

799
01:02:05,187 --> 01:02:07,563
It's been about 600 years, after all.

800
01:02:07,731 --> 01:02:11,401
I wonder where a guy,
an everyday Joe like myself...

801
01:02:11,568 --> 01:02:13,569
...can find a little action.

802
01:02:13,737 --> 01:02:15,071
WOMAN:
Hi.

803
01:02:15,948 --> 01:02:17,407
Yeah.

804
01:02:21,453 --> 01:02:23,246
WOMAN:
Come on. Come on in.

805
01:02:30,629 --> 01:02:32,755
Oh, yeah. Here I come, baby.

806
01:02:36,427 --> 01:02:39,095
Oh, yeah. Hey, Adam, nice move.

807
01:02:40,514 --> 01:02:43,057
-Adam, why did you build that?
-I didn't.

808
01:02:48,856 --> 01:02:52,191
WOMAN [OVER PA]: <i>All new arrivals report
to Waiting Room Number 8.</i>

809
01:02:53,193 --> 01:02:55,611
Will you guys shut up
and leave me alone?

810
01:02:55,779 --> 01:02:57,947
I've got all this paperwork to do.

811
01:03:00,409 --> 01:03:02,368
You two, come in here. Sit down.

812
01:03:02,536 --> 01:03:04,454
Get in here, both of you.

813
01:03:08,083 --> 01:03:12,628
The whorehouse was my idea.
I want Betelgeuse out of the picture.

814
01:03:13,380 --> 01:03:15,923
You two have really screwed up.

815
01:03:16,091 --> 01:03:18,968
I received word you allowed yourselves
to be photographed.

816
01:03:19,136 --> 01:03:21,971
And you let Betelgeuse out
and didn't put him back.

817
01:03:22,139 --> 01:03:24,432
And you let Otho
get hold of the handbook.

818
01:03:24,600 --> 01:03:25,892
The handbook? When?

819
01:03:26,894 --> 01:03:29,395
Never trust the living.

820
01:03:29,563 --> 01:03:32,231
We cannot have
a routine haunting like yours...

821
01:03:32,399 --> 01:03:36,486
...provide proof that there is existence
beyond death.

822
01:03:36,653 --> 01:03:40,031
-Coach. Coach, where's the men's room?
FOOTBALL PLAYER: Yeah.

823
01:03:40,199 --> 01:03:42,825
I'm not your coach. He survived.

824
01:03:42,993 --> 01:03:45,620
FOOTBALL PLAYER:
Wait, coach, let me get something straight.

825
01:03:45,788 --> 01:03:48,664
-What's our curfew around here?
-Will you get out of here?

826
01:03:49,583 --> 01:03:51,834
Go on, get downstairs. "Men's room."

827
01:03:52,002 --> 01:03:54,504
Are you kidding? Can't you read signs?

828
01:03:54,922 --> 01:03:56,672
I'll be right back.

829
01:03:57,174 --> 01:03:59,217
FOOTBALL PLAYER:
Come on. Get out of my way.

830
01:04:08,560 --> 01:04:10,812
Maybe this was all a bad idea.

831
01:04:10,979 --> 01:04:12,980
I didn't say anything.

832
01:04:14,942 --> 01:04:17,985
Oh, who are we kidding, Charles?
You've never had a bad idea.

833
01:04:18,153 --> 01:04:19,320
Yeah?

834
01:04:21,573 --> 01:04:23,741
Yeah, this could all work out.

835
01:04:25,369 --> 01:04:26,661
Home.

836
01:04:28,247 --> 01:04:29,372
Though...

837
01:04:30,124 --> 01:04:32,792
...I知 not sure that this is
the right environment for Lydia.

838
01:04:32,960 --> 01:04:35,503
-Snakes. Ghosts.
-Shrimp.

839
01:04:36,713 --> 01:04:38,297
You family types.

840
01:04:38,465 --> 01:04:42,260
You've got other things to worry about.
Maxie Dean's coming up here tonight.

841
01:04:42,427 --> 01:04:46,222
You've got to figure out a way to sell
these ghosts. I can only do so much.

842
01:04:46,390 --> 01:04:49,517
What are you gonna do, Otho?
Viciously rearrange their environment?

843
01:04:49,685 --> 01:04:54,021
I know just as much about the supernatural
as I do about interior design.

844
01:05:01,697 --> 01:05:03,239
"I am...

845
01:05:03,407 --> 01:05:05,116
...alone."

846
01:05:15,085 --> 01:05:16,961
"I am...

847
01:05:17,129 --> 01:05:18,880
...utterly...

848
01:05:19,047 --> 01:05:20,256
...alone.

849
01:05:21,717 --> 01:05:23,759
By the time...

850
01:05:25,095 --> 01:05:26,220
...you read this...

851
01:05:27,347 --> 01:05:29,098
...l will...

852
01:05:29,266 --> 01:05:31,100
...be gone...

853
01:05:32,102 --> 01:05:34,896
...having jumped--

854
01:05:36,148 --> 01:05:39,609
Having plummeted...

855
01:05:39,776 --> 01:05:41,694
...off...

856
01:05:41,862 --> 01:05:46,365
...the Winter River Bridge."

857
01:05:46,533 --> 01:05:49,202
So I don't care what it takes.

858
01:05:49,369 --> 01:05:52,038
You get the Deetzes out of there now.

859
01:05:52,206 --> 01:05:55,458
WOMAN [OVER PA]: Flight 409 arriving.
-Whoa, wait a minute.

860
01:05:56,043 --> 01:05:58,711
WOMAN [OVER PA]: Flight 409 is arriving.
-What are you going to do?

861
01:05:59,296 --> 01:06:01,088
To scare them.

862
01:06:01,256 --> 01:06:04,050
I want to make sure
it's not some silly parlor trick.

863
01:06:05,344 --> 01:06:06,385
I'll go first, honey.

864
01:06:16,563 --> 01:06:17,897
[ADAM GRUNTS]

865
01:06:20,442 --> 01:06:22,109
[SQUISHING]

866
01:06:29,159 --> 01:06:32,328
Not bad. Not bad. Now you.

867
01:06:33,497 --> 01:06:34,830
Go ahead.

868
01:06:48,553 --> 01:06:51,264
Okay, you look great.

869
01:06:51,431 --> 01:06:56,894
Now, go clean house and don't forget
the photographs and the damned handbook.

870
01:06:57,145 --> 01:06:59,814
WOMAN [OVER PA]:
Please report to Door Number 9.

871
01:07:00,232 --> 01:07:03,818
All new arrivals,
report to Waiting Room Number 8.

872
01:07:05,028 --> 01:07:07,947
-Coach?
JUNO: What?

873
01:07:08,115 --> 01:07:10,491
I don't think we survived that crash.

874
01:07:10,909 --> 01:07:12,451
How did you guess?

875
01:07:15,789 --> 01:07:17,707
Mr. and Mrs. Maitland?

876
01:07:22,462 --> 01:07:24,088
Hello?

877
01:07:24,840 --> 01:07:27,717
-Where are you?
BETELGEUSE: Dead.

878
01:07:28,385 --> 01:07:30,594
Dead, dead, deadski.

879
01:07:31,680 --> 01:07:33,639
Of course they're dead. They're ghosts.

880
01:07:33,807 --> 01:07:38,227
No, I mean they're gone. Split.
Out of here. Afterlife kids.

881
01:07:38,395 --> 01:07:41,731
-Deceased.
-Are you a ghost too?

882
01:07:42,649 --> 01:07:45,192
I'm the ghost with the most, babe.

883
01:07:47,529 --> 01:07:51,032
You know, you look like somebody
I can relate to.

884
01:07:52,075 --> 01:07:55,244
Maybe you could help me get out of here,
you know, because...

885
01:07:55,412 --> 01:07:58,080
...l gotta tell you, this, uh, death thing--

886
01:08:00,042 --> 01:08:01,375
[CRUNCHING]

887
01:08:01,543 --> 01:08:02,710
It's just too creepy.

888
01:08:03,128 --> 01:08:04,920
See, here's my problem.

889
01:08:05,088 --> 01:08:08,007
I got these friends on the outside
that I said I'd meet.

890
01:08:08,175 --> 01:08:10,468
You know, I have to be there
in person, you know.

891
01:08:10,635 --> 01:08:13,929
So I was just wondering,
could you help me get out of here?

892
01:08:14,348 --> 01:08:15,389
I wanna get in.

893
01:08:17,225 --> 01:08:18,267
Why?

894
01:08:18,810 --> 01:08:19,852
Well, you know...

895
01:08:20,020 --> 01:08:23,564
...hey, you've probably got your reasons,
but I can't do anything from over here.

896
01:08:23,732 --> 01:08:28,444
If you could get me out, over there,
then maybe we could talk or something.

897
01:08:28,612 --> 01:08:32,281
But, you know, in order to do that
you've gotta say my name three times.

898
01:08:32,449 --> 01:08:34,325
What's your name?

899
01:08:34,493 --> 01:08:37,787
-Well, uh, I can't tell you.
-Why not?

900
01:08:37,954 --> 01:08:42,416
Because if I tell you, you'll tell your friends,
they're calling me on the horn all the time.

901
01:08:42,584 --> 01:08:46,295
I've gotta show up at shopping centers
for openings, sign autographs, shit like that.

902
01:08:46,463 --> 01:08:49,965
And it makes my life a hell, okay?
A living hell.

903
01:08:50,133 --> 01:08:54,804
But maybe if you have a pen, maybe
we can-- I know. You ever play charades?

904
01:08:54,971 --> 01:08:56,764
-Yeah.
-Good. Good.

905
01:08:56,932 --> 01:08:58,557
Ahh, here we go then. Ready?

906
01:08:58,892 --> 01:09:02,395
-Um, two words.
-Right.

907
01:09:03,980 --> 01:09:06,357
First word, two syllables.

908
01:09:06,608 --> 01:09:08,401
Look.

909
01:09:08,568 --> 01:09:10,820
You know, just turn around.

910
01:09:11,780 --> 01:09:13,489
I don't know what your signal means.

911
01:09:13,657 --> 01:09:15,449
Turn around and look behind you.

912
01:09:16,701 --> 01:09:18,327
Hi. How are you?

913
01:09:19,162 --> 01:09:21,914
-Beetle.
-Got it. Okay, now, two.

914
01:09:25,168 --> 01:09:27,503
Breakfast? Orange? Orange beetle?

915
01:09:27,671 --> 01:09:29,505
Beetle fruit?

916
01:09:30,173 --> 01:09:31,507
Beetle breakfast?

917
01:09:32,300 --> 01:09:33,676
Beetle drink?

918
01:09:34,511 --> 01:09:35,761
Beetle--

919
01:09:36,513 --> 01:09:38,139
Beetle juice?

920
01:09:38,306 --> 01:09:40,808
-Yes. That's it.
-Your name's Betelgeuse?

921
01:09:40,976 --> 01:09:43,811
You said it twice.
Just say it once more. Come on.

922
01:09:43,979 --> 01:09:45,688
It was you, wasn't it?

923
01:09:45,856 --> 01:09:47,648
-Wha--? Me?
-The snake.

924
01:09:47,816 --> 01:09:50,651
No, what snake?
You kids and your imagination.

925
01:09:50,819 --> 01:09:52,278
Just say it.

926
01:09:52,696 --> 01:09:53,988
No.

927
01:09:55,031 --> 01:09:56,365
I want to talk to Barbara.

928
01:09:56,533 --> 01:10:00,035
No, you don't need to talk to Barbara.
Just say it.

929
01:10:03,540 --> 01:10:07,168
Oh, Adam, I can't go through with it.
I like that little girl.

930
01:10:07,335 --> 01:10:10,880
But, Barbara, honey, it's too late.
We have to go through with this.

931
01:10:11,047 --> 01:10:15,050
No, we don't.
I mean, can't we rebel or something?

932
01:10:15,469 --> 01:10:17,136
[ADAM SIGHS]

933
01:10:17,721 --> 01:10:19,513
Barbara.

934
01:10:20,390 --> 01:10:22,683
Adam, I want to be with Lydia.

935
01:10:33,570 --> 01:10:36,155
Come on. Just say it.

936
01:10:37,073 --> 01:10:39,408
ADAM: No!
BARBARA: No! Lydia, don't say it.

937
01:10:39,576 --> 01:10:42,511
Fuck you. Say it!

938
01:10:42,579 --> 01:10:45,456
It's okay. It's okay. It's us.
What's going on?

939
01:10:46,583 --> 01:10:48,083
-Betel--
-Shh!

940
01:10:48,251 --> 01:10:52,004
He told me that if I let him out he would
take me to the other side to find you.

941
01:10:52,547 --> 01:10:55,382
No, Lydia, we're dead.

942
01:10:56,468 --> 01:10:59,470
-I wanna be dead too.
-No.

943
01:11:00,889 --> 01:11:02,515
Lydia...

944
01:11:07,103 --> 01:11:10,105
...being dead really doesn't
make things any easier.

945
01:11:10,565 --> 01:11:15,110
Listen to her on this, Lydia.
This is something we know a lot about.

946
01:11:15,278 --> 01:11:18,781
And you can come up here
and visit us anytime you want.

947
01:11:19,491 --> 01:11:22,826
I have a feeling things are going to be
a little better around here from now on.

948
